text.tspan: Princess Knight, first published in 1953, tells the story of a
baby girl princess who is raised as a boy. As seen in the
image above, Osamu Tezuka experiments with themes of
gender bending by portraying the protagonist as androgy
nous, with both traditionally male and female characteristics.
